1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with interference alignment and detection in MIMO interference channels, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a scheme for interference management in wireless networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper involves signal processing techniques for interference detection and cancellation. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the impact of discrete constellation inputs on the symbol error rate, which is relevant to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses graph theory and semi-definite relaxation techniques for user set selection and interference detection, which are computational engineering techniques.
